social_posts.post_text:
📍Little Prince, West Village
⭐️8.4/10
Little Prince was really good! The spot was easy to get a reservation, nice inside, and had good food. My favorite thing we got was the mussel appetizer because the playing was great, it was very flavorful, and there were plenty of mussels. Then I really enjoyed my French onion soup. The top cheese was a little burnt but the soup had so much flavor. The turbo was delicious and very meaty, and came on a filling potato galette. My least favorite dish was the tuna tartar which I just didn’t find special. Would recommend this spot! 👑 my first French place in while

📍Ajax Tavern, Aspen
⭐️9.6/10
really craving my favorite grilled cheese and tomato soup in the world from @thelittlenell ‘s Ajax tavern on this cold nyc day🥪

📍Au Cheval, Soho
⭐️8.1/10
Finally made it to @auchevaldiner and I don’t think it lived up to the hype. The burger was good, but it wasn’t the best I’ve had. I will say I feel like when it gets to the top ranked burgers in a city like nyc, it comes down to preference over actual issues with the burger. For me? I much prefer @minettatavernny or @emmysquaredpizza The fries were delicious with the most garlicky aioli ever, but the whipped mashed potatoes we didn’t like and barely even ate.

📍Mokyo, East Village 
⭐️9.4/10 
Went to @mokyonyc after enjoying @thursdaykitchen , and it was even better. The yellowtail crudo with salsa  really blew me away, and so did the super fresh noodles with the perfect spice kick. The ribs were so tender and juicy, and the oxtail rolls were beyond crunchy. We also had a hazelnut dessert and a beet chopped up on tostada. This spot was a great fusion experience and I highly recommend🥢

📍The Dolar Shop, East Village
⭐️8.3/10
Hadn’t had hotpot in so long and was so excited I finally went to @thedolarshopusa ! I thought the hot pot was good and the restaurant was really nice. I wish the descriptors of what I was getting with my broth were better so I didn’t over order, and I wish there was a communal broth which makes it more fun! Overall a good experience and a nice change of pace 💛

Thank you @beergarageny for having me in! This casual spot in the west village is perfect for an affordable and quick drink.🍻 They also serve some bar food style bites like yummy parmesan fries.🍟 If you go… you gotta get the mac and cheese balls !🧀

@originalbalsamicvinegar is the perfect thing to elevate your kitchen game! 🙌🏼the balsamic vinegar has an EU PGI stamp that indicated the BV is made with a high standard of quality, and that it respects the traditional production process! 🇮🇹The BV is rich in flavor, and a great addition to any meal. I’ve already made an Italian inspired dipping oil with it and devoured the whole thing! 🥖 highly recommend, high quality balsamic vinegar makes all the difference❤️
#balsamicvinegarofmodena 
#enjoyitsfromeurope 
#blackgold

@xuspublichouse is right off of union square and delicious! The prawn dumplings featured first had fun colors and great flavor.🥟 We got to try so much. The soup dumplings, sesame balls, and scallion pancakes were my favorite (some of the best scallion pancakes I’ve had in a long time). 🥡It has a HUGE menu with every dish you could want. Delicious modern Chinese spot; thank you for inviting me in! ❤️

@thenookeastvillage is absolutely PHENOMENAL.🤩 I have not tried a new restaurant in so long that blew me away like this. 🤯Every dish at this Korean fusion spot was so delicious, well thought through, and executed to perfection. The vibes there are so good too. 🔥
Dishes in order:
1) beef tartare with sesame paste and fried seaweed (my favorite dish. Amazing.)🤌🏼
2) scallop crudo with an amazing lime/jalapeño sauce
3) the nook cocktail (with a Negroni in the back) - one of the best cocktails I’ve ever had with 4 day chamomile infused gin and custom pressed ice with their logo🥃
4) prawns with boulibase and rice paper chips
5) lump crab fried rice 🦀 
6) miso cod - better than nobu it was so delicious and tender
7) veal cheek in polenta that just melted in your mouth
8) miso tres leches  which is one of the BEST desserts I’ve had in so long🍦
I cannot recommend this place enough. You will be blown away by your visit, and now is the time before it becomes the hottest spot! 💝

@crackricenyc is upping the nyc fast casual food game 🔥 this spot has places all over the city in poke restaurants, but this one was right off union square! I got 4 spicy salmon, 4 spicy tuna, and 4 sauces to try!🤩 My favorite sauces were the eel sauce and spicy mayo. This box was super well priced and left me very full!🤰🏼 The fish tasted good quality, and the rice was super crispy!🍣 check it out if you want a new quick bite!

Hiyake on Bowery has now opened a spot in Williamsburg! The spot has an array of dishes as well as quality meats for some delicious Japanese bbq!🥩 My favorites were the short rib and the negamaki- which was teriyaki soaked meat with scallions inside 🤤 we also enjoyed king oyster mushrooms, some karaage, and baby octopus 😳🐙meal was really good and I recommend to anyone who’s looking for some Japanese bbq in the area! ☺️

Thank you so much @butterdosenyc for having me! 💛 this new French Asian fusion bakery in the east village is delicious. I got to try so much- but my favorites had to be the egg tarte (so sweet and delicious), my latte (with pretty art), and the pesto biscuit sandwich 🤤 there’s so much to choose from, and it has lots of seating if you want an easy place to eat/work!🪑 strongly recommend, and I can’t wait to go back! 🏃‍♂️

📍Great White, Venice
⭐️9.6/10
LA food is delicious. Great white is an amazing brunch spot right in all the action in Venice. 🌊You will probably have to wait for a table, but they keep it moving. The menu has a lot to choose from- ranging from basics to unique things. This salmon pizza with crème was so delicious and flavorful 🍕 , the banana bread was sweet with perfectly whipped butter🧈 , and the curry salmon had so many herbs and was so flavorful.🌿 The salmon was cooked to perfection and it had a perfect amount of kick. HIGHLY recommend great white! 🦈

📍Jon & Vinny’s, Bentwood
⭐️8.6/10
The @jonandvinnydelivery ‘s spicy fusili does live up to the hype🔥

📍Jing, Aspen
⭐️9.9/10
Every time I go to Jing I love trying something new, and it never disappoints. ❤️ Making my way through the wholeeee menu. This time we tried the miso salmon and softshell crab tempura! 🦀 They were both excellent but other dishes are still my favs… including the French onion soup dumplings 🥟 featured in slide 3! This is a MUST VISIT if you’re in aspen! 🎿

📍PARC, Aspen 
⭐️8.6/10
I always love trying a new place in Aspen and @parcaspen did not disappoint!❤️ The vibe inside is not pretentious, and the staff were so nice. The Napa valley cabernet wine list offerings blew me away 🍷 , and so did the menu items they all had a fun twist. In order: braised short rib, short rib anoliti (best we had), apple crostini, butternut squad soup, and a truffle duck pasta special! 🍝 really solid spot and can see it lasting in Aspen for a while! 💪

📍Jacobs Pickles, UWS
⭐️8.6/10
Back in nyc and already thinking about @jacobspickles ‘s amazing Mac… this southern food restaurant was delicious! ❤️ I had fried chicken with sausage gravy that was SO GOOD! 🐔 would definitely come back, and highly recommend !😍

📍Kith Treats, Noho 
⭐️9.4/10
This famous street brand @kith is also known for their icecream, @kithtreats . ❤️ They run a counter out of the second floor of their store. You pick a flavor, a type of cereal, and then a mixin and they make it- soft serve style. 🍦 Mine is vanilla with fruit loops and rainbow sprinkles. 🌈 this treat is so creamy and flavorful I HIGHLY recommend!

📍Din Tai Fung, Century City LA
⭐️ 9.3/10
I’ve wanted to try din tai fung for 6 years and I’m so glad I finally got to.😍 The xiao long bao, garlic green beans, and spicy wontons were a knock out of the park. ⚾️ Everything was so clearly fresh and home made- the noodles didn’t blow me away though. The place is a machine and I can tell why it’s become such an iconic world wide spot! 🥟

Thank you @seawolfus for having me in!❤️ They offer a $49 lobster Monday deal that include unlimited alcohol for 90 min! (R u kidding me?!🍷🥂🍻) The spot is right on the Williamsburg water way which adds a beautiful view. The lobster Mac was yummy, 🦞 and they have @stevesauthentic key lime pie (had been DYING to try) which had my mouth watering at the end of the meal🤤 #seawolfbk

@skinnyscantina in LIC had such a fun vibe with decorations everywhere🎊 The cocktails were yummy and well priced- also sangria was super sweet🍷 the Queso was so good and thick, and the esquites were delicious! 🌽then, I had the shrimp for my main, had me so full!🍤

📍Republique Bakery, LA
⭐️9.5/10
LA has done it YET AGAIN with a phenomenal brunch spot. @republiquecafebakery was a hit. 🤩You start in line for the bakery- and can buy baked goods to eat at your table.🥐 You order your food at the bakery and then it’s open seating. I had an amazing pistachio and raspberry kouign-aman and apple danish from the bakery, then Shakshuka and their potato pancake for my main. The potato pancake was a PHENOMENAL dish with so many layers. I loved it and highly recommend republique🎊

I was so honored to be invited by Iron Chef @mingtsai for a tour of NYC’s Chinatown last week❤️ while I could only hit one spot, I was hyped it was one of my favorites, Peking Duck House 🦆 The duck is so tender and crispy (and it’s BYOB👀) if you haven’t explored- china town has some of the best, and most affordable, food in the city! so many places including peking duck house and mei lei wah, are must haves for me! Thank you again @mingtsai and the @mingsbings team💪

📍La la land cafe, The Grove LA
⭐️5/10
I was so excited to visit @lalalandkindcafe but was extremely disappointed😢 The place is so cute but the line is insane. The special latte was barely drinkable. Better for clothes and fun things than actually drinking. ☕️🤷🏼‍♀️

📍Violet Bistro, Westwood LA
⭐️7.6/10
Went to @violetbistro in Westwood and was disappointed.🥲 The artichokes were amazing. They were cooked to perfection and the aioli was so good. Our steak though, came out cold. For what we paid, it shouldn’t have. The fries were good, but would have been better if they were warm.🤷🏼‍♀️ Then I personally didn’t like the mussels sauce, I didn’t think it was flavorful enough. They did have a really cute indoor/outdoor space for seating, and strong cocktails. Would be a nice spot for a drinks and apps date! 🍸

I have so many good things to say about @ipanema 💛 first off, the ambiance was amazing. the restaurant is so pretty! second, we really enjoyed our food. the first, moqueca, was my favorite. it had so many different seafoods, and was so flavorful. the potato au gratin with our steak was some of the best I’ve ever had. lastly, we ended with a delicious dessert tasting plate where the presentation just speaks for itself! great spot worth adding to your lists☺️

Poke Bowl is an awesome poke spot with so many nyc locations!🐠 I went to the one in union square and got to pick everything I wanted. The fish, fruits, and veggies all tasted very fresh! such an easy spot to grab some lunch where you can actually sit down! (They also sell @crackricenyc out of here 🫢)

📍Katsuya, Brentwood
⭐️9.2/10
Finally made it to katsuya! @katsuyabrentwood was so yum.🫶🏼 not everything pictured, but the sashimis, cocktails, and rock shrimp were phenomenal. we also got spicy edamame which I’d never have, but elevated a classic dish!💛 easy to get into last minute, highly recommend.

📍19 Clevland, Soho
⭐️9.5/10
Went to @19cleveland on Friday and it was delicious Israeli cuisine🔥 the restaurant was SO fun too- it had loud music and an amazing magician going around doing tricks🪄highly recommend this spot for a meal with friends for good food and fun times 🫶🏼

📍EssaBagel, New York
⭐️10/10
My favorite bagels strike again… the fluffiest plain bagel toasted with scallion cream cheese and lox from @essabagel1stave 🫶🏼

📍MIA Kitchen & Bar, Delray 
⭐️8.6/10
one of the best meals I’ve had in delray! the elevated dishes at @miakitchenandbar were delicious, and there were so many dishes I didn’t get that I wanted to try!🫶🏼the cocktails were great, our buratta had saffron and pesto in a watermelon gazpacho, and my branzino was served in a Cantonese style. will definitely be going back on my next trip‼️

📍Bonnie’s, Brooklyn 
⭐️9.3/10
I was so happy to finally get into @bonniesbrooklyn 🫶🏼 the spot lives up to all the hype with amazing dishes- the espresso martini (best of my life), mushrooms with sticky rice, and mcrib were spectacular with bold delicious flavors 🥢 if you have the chance, go! you won’t regret it

thank you @northforknyc for having me in!🍴 this cute spot on Christopher street has a unique menu and yummy food- everything had a twist!🌸 our pappardelle ragu was made with wild boar, the halibut had a beet purée (delicious), and the crème brûlée was espresso. My favorite dish was their mussels! They had a spicy kick, lots of flavor, and were very fresh❤️easy and more affordable spot to stop in if you’re in the wv!

📍La Esquina, Soho
⭐️7.5/10
This speakeasy spot in Soho is so fun, but I wouldn’t say the food is amazing. You definitely go for the vibes, as people are dancing, and the music is fun. It’s downstairs behind an unassuming Mexican restaurant, that I’ve passed 1 million times and never realized. The drinks are good too! First photo is pork belly tacos🌮 @esquinanyc

📍Ellina, Aspen
⭐️9.7/10
One of my favorite aspen spots is @ellinaaspen !🎿 some of my favorite calamari in a spicy chili sauce, a delicious short rib that melted to the touch, and the amazing flavorful polenta balls are all hits. definitely check it out on your next visit to aspen!🌼

📍Serafina, LES
⭐️3.7/10
It’s been a while since I slandered a restaurant, but @serafinanewyork deserves it. For having so many locations at this point, you think they would’ve learned to make the food better? Everything was beyond subpar, but that alone doesn’t earn it a 3.7. Our waitress was wonderful, but the manager was horrible. We had a reservation for 7 people, and my friend and I got there early. The manager was sitting at the bar, and a big party of pretty girls and their friends were waiting for a table to open up, they were going to be placed outside and it was freezing. He seemed to be flirting w them. TWO MINUTES after our reservation time, and 2/7 were already there, he comes over and in an extremely nasty tone reprimands us and let’s us know our table time is going to be cut short for our party not being there on time- as if he was trying to get the table for the group of attractive girls. We say our reservation started two minutes ago, and the two of us hadn’t even been given menus yet to order. He says he just needed to let us know that if our party wasn’t there and we didn’t start ordering we could lose our table??? His tone and threats made us feel very uncomfortable and unwelcome. There was supposed to be a 15 minute grace period, and 3 more members of our party were there within the next 5 minutes. We then immediately began ordering. It made us extremely uncomfortable and I will not be returning to any serafina, or recommending it, anytime soon.

📍Fia, Santa Monica 
⭐️8.9/10
Made it to @fiarestaurant ! The food was good, but the truffle corn and salmon cones were GREAT! The drinks were both delicious too. The garden outdoors was so intimate but unfortunately we sat on the side. Overall, food was good but overpriced. I think there’s better in LA but it’s def a nice experience! 🫶🏼

📍Gemma Restaurant, Bowery
⭐️5.3/10
The only perk of going here is you can get a reservation for brunch, which isn’t always common in nyc. It’s a big space in the Bowery Hotel. Food and service were extremely average. Wouldn’t go back, but don’t mind that I went 🥞

📍Gjusta, Venice
⭐️8.6/10
Hit @gjustabakery after loving gjelina and it’s still good, but different. You get a ticket and you wait to order, but it’s not an efficient system ( so be prepared) I made my own sandwich and the baguette was 🤌🏼 also had the shortbread sandwich pastry with whipped cream and raspberry’s and it was >>> def expensive for semi stingy servings so just be prepared. Everything was clearly very fresh, and the outside was so nice! 🌳

📍Bicyclette, LA
⭐️9.5/10
everything made by @bicyclette.la was perfectly executed. the apple tarte had a thyme ice cream that elevated it, and my salmon was phenomenal. We started off with the mussels that had a lot of flavor, but were even better when you dipped the freshly made baguette into them. The beef bourguignon was cooked to perfection and deliciously tender. Such a great spot, highly recommend + points for easier to get into! 🚲

Thank you for inviting me in @cheftan_eastvillage ! 🌶️ This huge east village spot has an amazing menu that features some awesome szechuan and hunan dishes.🥢 Everything is well priced and delicious! The pork belly was so tender, and the scallion pancakes were some of the best I’ve ever had (since they were so crispy). Great spot, highly recommend! #ad

📍Butchers Daughter, Nolita
⭐️8.8/10
Happy Saturday, here’s some brunch inspo for you ☀️@thebutchersdaughter_official quinoa bowl have me the health and energy I needed, but the swipe to the right shows what I really loved… the loaded banana bread 🤩 it’s a small spot, just be warned! Didn’t seem to have personal indoor tables, but it does take reservations which was great 🎊

📍Restoration Hardware, Yountville
⭐️9.6/10
Another amazing meal @rh_restorationhardware yountville❤️ the setting is beautiful and all the food is delicious. It has an amazing menu filled with classics and some unique takes and I can’t recommend it enough. I had this heavy loaded lobster roll that I would highly recommend!🦞

📍Darioush, Napa Valley
@darioushwinery had some of the best food I’ve ever had in a tasting🍽️ the mushrooms with truffle and the adult cheese sauce were my favorite, followed by the carrot purée with veggies!🫶🏼 while they weren’t my favorite wines, I still think the experience was wonderful! I also loved drinking in the vineyard for a bit, it was something I’d never done 🍃
thank you for having me at your second locations media opening! @alloranyc 🤍ft. the pesto gnocchi (but my heart was with the grilled octopus… just didn’t get a good pic!)

📍Goose and Gander, Napa
⭐️9.8/10
Goose and gander never disappoints! The St. Helena restaurant has a large menu with unique dishes. The octopus, cauliflower, and STICKY PIG EARS were my favorites! (If you go and you don’t get the pig ears…🙅🏼‍♀️🙅🏼‍♀️) highly recommend for a delicious, unique, and flavorful dinner

📍Citifield, Queens
Happy baseball season! Who doesn’t love paying $8 for a hot dog? (Me) 🌭 but yes, I’m gonna do it… I don’t know how hotdogs always taste better at baseball games but go Mets! @mets ⚾️

@tonchinbrooklyn blew me away. while this spot is known for its ramen, it’s everything else that makes the spot so unique! the hamachi, banana pudding, cucumbers, and carpaccio were all phenomenal, along with the service and the vibes🫶🏼 highly recommend this spot for unique dishes and an awesome meal🍾 (also… LOOK at that plating 🔥)

📍AdHoc, Napa
⭐️9.9/10
The things I would do to be back @adhoc_addendum in Napa… Thomas Keller has hit it out of the part every time!😍 It’s family style with a different menu everyday. We had ribs, an herbaceous salad, mouth watering chicken, phenomenal Mac and cheese, delicious cheese, and an amazing key lime mousse 💚 everything is made excellently, and the service matches. One of the best restaurants in Napa without a doubt! 👏🏼

📍Upland, Flatiron
@upland_nyc has a special spot in my 🫶🏼 with a phenomenal vibe, amazing drinks, and well priced food, this restaurant is such a great spot. loved the bolognese and adult Nutter butters the best (after amazing drinks). Highly recommend, especially for a date night (everyone was a couple)! 🥹

📍Mister Softee, NYC 
The first @mrsofteetruck of summer! Nothings better than a cold ice cream on a hot day (and mister softee has the best soft serve around…🍦)

had the best time checking out @alidoronyc this weekend! the staff could not have been friendlier (and the bread could not have been better😦)! 🥖 I made my own sandwich that included prosciutto, mozzarella, pesto lemon, tomatoes, EVOO, balsamic, and best of all … sweet onions (onions marinated in balsamic!) they have so many locations around the city- check them out if you have the chance ‼️🥪

Thank you @newwonjo for having me! Wonjo is the only Korean bbq restaurant in NY that has a legal permit for using charcoal indoors, and you can really taste the unique flavors on the meat! They’re also the oldest Korean BBQ restaurant in NYC… so you know they’re good.❤️ The meats had phenomenal taste, and so did all the additional dishes (dukbokki >>>). All their BBQ meat is farm-to-table from a privately owned Nebraska farm too!🥩 I highly recommend Wonjo as a next dinner stop- KBBQ is always good, but Wonjo takes it to the NEXT LEVEL‼️

@foodgallery32.ktownnyc is an awesome food hall in ktown!🎉 we got to try so many different bites from different stands, and they were all really well priced!☺️ ended up so satisfied and full.  They also have fun social activities, such as nail art, karaoke, and a photobooth!🎤We had dukkbokki from Seoul, sushi from rollnkatsu, buns from mamma, and my favorite CHURROS!!! (From the awesome @sweetchurrosnyc )🫶🏼 highly recommend the trip to explore and support some awesome Korean vendors, while enjoying tasty and affordable food (and who can complain about it all being in one place…)🔥

📍Patrizias, Kips Bay
@patriziasrestaurants remains one of the most fun spots for a group dinner! with an unlimited all you can eat and drink menu, and fun loud music, you can’t go wrong. also, the food is ACTUALLY good. but personally - I think their pizza > their pasta🍕

📍Beatnic, Williamsburg 
@eatbeatnic ‘s peanut crunch on @mealpal ! @mealpal has absolutely changed the lunch game. with so many awesome restaurants, and all pre-ordering, mealpal has made lunch so easy! you can scroll around the map and see what restaurants are offering near you then set a pick up time! the food has been awesome. checkout mealpal.com/tastessky for 5 free meals! ❤️

📍La Toque, Napa
⭐️100000/10
If I could give @latoquerestaurant an a million out of ten I would. Everything at this one star ⭐️ Michelin restaurant is spectacular. I’ve done the tasting menu, and this time I came a la carte! We got duck and an amazing veal chop for 2 as our mains, a bolognese, every. single. dessert. on the menu, and my favorite carpaccio in the world🫶🏼 counting down the days until I can go back…

thank you so much for having me in @beyondsushinyc 🫶🏼 I was beyond shocked by how yummy this vegan spot was! They have a large menu of vegan alternatives, and also just authentically vegan dishes! The sweet chili cauliflower with dill sauce is a MUST HAVE! Literally life changing. 🤩

📍Loveski, Napa
⭐️8.9/10
Nothing compares to a NY bagel, but @loveski.deli is creating a spot over on the west coast! The deli is in ox bow market, an awesome food hall in downtown Napa. They boast unique bagel combos, but most importantly, amazing latkes. Literally tried one then got up and ordered another because it was so good. Highly suggest it as a morning spot before drinking! @visitnapavalley
I’m sorry but I’m still thinking about this cheese boat from @oldtbilisigarden ! They knew what they were doing with this - bread and hot gooey cheese is the ultimate combo always >>>

📍Maison Close, Soho
⭐️6.6/10
I had such high hopes for @maisoncloserestaurant only to be met with some of the worst service in manhattan. While the inside was swanky and glamorous, the food left a lot to be desired. Save your money, and go elsewhere. (Ft. Scallops and tuna crudo)

📍Shoo Shoo, Nolita
⭐️9/10
Looking for a good, easy to get, brunch reservation in nolita? Look no further. Have had @shooshoonolita for dinner, but finally went for lunch, and HIGHLY recommend (way better than butchers daughter across the street…🤫) - we had hummus, the chicken schnitzel sandwich, and the Israeli salad on a bed of tahini which is spectacular.

📍Tuome, East Village
⭐️9.7/10
I HIGHLY recommend @tuomenyc . The 1 Michelin star 🌟 restaurant has had its star three years in a row, and you can tell. The snow crab noodle dish featured first was our favorite- with a delicious serving of crab and perfect noodles, they tasted creamy and buttery without being heavy at all. 🦀 The pig out for 2 is delicious, along with the special dumplings. Had to end with the DIY beignet ice cream sandwiches >  this place is a HIDDEN GEM because what other amazing Michelin star restaurant can you get in a week before or day of? Run don’t walk to Tuome 🏃🏽‍♀️

📍Katz’s Delicatessen, LES
⭐️8.8/10
I get the hype, I do, I just had issues with the crazy disorganization and waiting. Like I got to order my sandwich then had to go somewhere else for latkes so my sandwich like isn’t hot if I want to eat them tg? Was just weird to me. Sandwich itself is good I just wish the bread didn’t fall apart immediately. Loved the latkes and the pastrami itself though. Glad I finally hit this iconic spot :) #katz #katzdelicatessen

📍Ludlow Coffee Supply, LES
Been to @ludlowcoffeesupply multiple times now, and I think it’s great! Really solid coffee shop. Had a vanilla latte with almond milk that was fab, and this matcha was pretty good (+ had only a $5.50 price point for including almond milk?! go off) Will def become a neighborhood joint for me highly recommend > 🍵

Thank you so much @cheestories_eu for inviting me to your wonderful event. 💛 I had the opportunity to try so many cheeses from Southern Europe, specifically Spain. Cheese stories is about a journey starring the Smiths, a family of Americans living in Southern Europe, in Spain. They took an incredible journey of more than 900 miles around Southern Europe trying cheeses. I highly suggest you go out and get some European cheese from Spain, and if you’re in NYC, check out Despana for some! Ready to Play? 🧀 #Cheestories #EuropeanCheese #CheesesFromSpain #Cheese #EuropeanQuality

📍Mercato della Boqueria, Barcelona 
Leaving Europe today so I will become more active again! Featured here is manchego from one of the food stands at the Boqueria in Barcelona. The Boqueria is a large street food vendors market that had everything from cheeses and meats to salmon tartare tacos. It was one of the food highlights of my trip and I highly recommend!

📍Bel Mondo, Madrid
⭐️8/10
The famous @bigmamma.uk known for Pink Mamma in Paris, also has a similar style Madrid restaurant with the famous Malfadini so I finally got to try it! The space has really cool decor, but the service was lacking. The Malfadini itself was good but not great- it’s incredibly rich and hard to eat as a dish on its own. It does have good flavors though. Worth trying it if you’ve wanted to, but not some special culinary feat!

📍Les Amoureux, Nice
⭐️9.8/10
The best pizza I’ve ever had in my life was at Les Amoureux in Nice. The neopolitan pizza comes in the shape of a heart, if you want it too, and it’s fantastic. It’s super popular so we got there before it opened and waited. It’s affordable and fantastic. This is the truffle with prosciutto instead of sausage! Necessary stop on s trip to nice :)

📍Brasserie Dubillot, París
⭐️8.6/10
Delicious, affordable, and swanky! Points off for medium service, as it was super hard to get our waiter, and mid aperol spritzes, but super happy I went 🫶🏼

📍Emily, West Village
@pizzalovesemily is my favorite burger in the city by far. They make a phenomenal burger on a pretzel bun with pickles (and I don’t even really like pretzel buns or pickles so that’s how you know…) highly recommend. go asap 🍔
@kaitenzushi_nomad has now opened in nomad! highly recommend checking it out again🍣❤️

📍Stohrer, París
@stohrer is the oldest patisserie in Paris, and I was so excited to get to visit! I got my favorite pastry, a kouign aman. 🥐 An iconic spot in the 2nd I highly recommend 🫶🏼 #stohrer #paris

📍Baieta, París 
1 Michelin star @baieta_restaurant probably won’t get its star again. We were extremely underwhelmed by both the food, and the experience. Watch the video to hear more, and skip it on your next trip 🤷🏼‍♀️

📍 H&H Bagels
Thank you for having me in @handhbagels ! H&H used to fly their dough down to a cafe in miami, and they would bake it in their own oven, while I was growing up, so H&H reminds me of my childhood. Loved my sesame with scallion lox and tomato, and also loved my sweet bagel. There’s a few throughout the city but be sure to check out this location next time you’re in the UWS! It’s also one block from the park so it’s the perfect treat to bring along for your next picnic 🤍🥯
went back to @arthurandsons in the west village, and it was great yet again! don’t skip out on the gnocchi… hidden killer 💛

📍Casa Nicasio, Madrid 
⭐️9/10
Loved learning the local spot of Casa Nicasio from a wonderful tapas tour I took in Madrid! The chorizos were spectacular, the spanish omelette was delicious, and the paella was the best we had. Highly recommend on your next trip to Madrid! 🇪🇸
Finally tried @nowon.usa and I WILL be back for this burger🍔 it was so good, and the vibes were so fun. super easy to get into too, so highly recommend! 🪩
@matsunori.nyc is killing the game with a delicious $88 , 15 piece omakase in the LES. Two appetizers, 10 nigiri, 2 handrolls, and cantaloupe dessert 🫶🏼 #matsunori #LES

📍Bar Cafe LILO, Madrid 
⭐️5.6/10
I was so surprised to find out Madrid had so many cute instagrammy cafes, but the food was only fine at the ones I tried. Bar LILO had purple velvet everywhere and huge teddy bears but the banana bread was dry.
@lesartizans is a hidden gem! super affordable, easy to get into, and great food in Paris. vibes are very casual and it’s a perfect easy dinner spot 🇫🇷 #paris #lesartizans

I loved checking out @sakebarsatsko with @btwn_app ! BTWN literally gets you rebates as you eat, and you don’t even have to do anything. Sake Bar Satsko had so much personality and felt iconic. Highly recommend for a bite and a drink with friends🤍 #btwnapp #sakebarsatsko

📍RH Rooftop, Meatpacking 
⭐️9.5/10
restorationhardware is one of my favorite spots to eat in Napa, so I loved checking out the NYC location! The store is beautiful, and the roof has amazing views. The food hit the spot, just like it did there. Highly recommend as nice easy to get into dinner!
Here are the best things I ate at Mercado de La Boqueria in Spain! Highly recommend this amazing food market on your trip ✈️ #barcelona #mercadodelaboqueria

the most exciting package of my “career” was the @essabagel X @magnoliabakery banana pudding cream cheese bagel 🥯🍌 this is a new yorker, and sweet bagel lover’s, dream. the cream cheese is delicious and the bagels are as doughy as ever. highly recommend checking out @essabagel1stave , @essabagel at 32nd, or on @goldbelly if you’re not in nyc 🗽 TRY IT NOW!!!✨
@bartulix is absolutely so swanky and should totally make the @beli_eats best places for last minute reservation list 🤍 i stg those branzino tacos were OUT of this world… just the pricing was too🙃
I always post about @mealpal but here’s me unboxing my order from @eatlittlekirin ! Use code TASTESSKY for 5 free meals when you sign up. That’s a WHOLE week free! ❤️
thank you so much @cocacola for the awesome PR package! go check out the @leagueoflegends X @cocacola collab along with the new sleek tall cans 🥤❤️
I finally got to try @dhamakanyc by @unapologeticfoodsnyc and left impressed by the flavors but honestly underwhelmed by the ambiance, and super hungry. Watch to see everything I got!

📍Arthur & Sons, West Village
⭐️9.2/10
loved going back to Arthur and sons and trying some new dishes! the gnocchi dish was awesome, I think I liked it more than the famous rig. but my favorite will always be the ice cream dessert 🤌🏼

@pusu.vegetarian is an awesome new vegetarian fusion spot in Williamsburg! with unique dishes,  swanky interior, and yummy cocktails, you’ve gotta check it out. thank you so much for having me, highly recommend! 🥟🍹

📍Win Son, Williamsburg
⭐️9.2/10
You win son, you lose some, but I did NOT lose anything @winsonbrooklyn ! This meal was delicious - the sloppy bao and wagyu tartare were my favorites, but everything was great. Highly recommend the Asian fusion spot for your next nyc dinner! 🤍🫶🏼

thank you so much @likealocaltours for having me 🤍 I loved touring Williamsburg and learning so much more about the city. and ESPECIALLY loved checking some places off my to try list ✔️highly recommend taking one and learning more about your city!
wishing the @essabagel X @magnoliabakery collab went on forever… the banana pudding cream cheese was too good! 🍌💛
had the most amazing stay this weekend with @getawayhouse 🫶🏼 thank you so much! it was such an amazing experience, and I highly recommend checking it out and escaping the city 🏙️

EVERYONE!!! RELAX!!! THE DAY HAS COME!!! 💗Throughout October, Ess-a-Bagel is offering limited edition PINK bagels and Cherry Almond Cream Cheese… and yes it’s as good as it looks. The cream cheese is sweet and flavorful (without being overpoweringly so), and the bagel is NEON pink. 🎀Even better, 15% of proceeds from these bagels will be donated to the @americancancersociety ‘s making strides against breast cancer of Central Park! 🥯Run, don’t walk, to get yours and try if now!
thank you for having me @3giovani ‼️🫶🏼

📍CP Burger, Aspen
@cp.burger ‘s milkshakes always hit- this is a cookies and cream but with vanilla ice cream (ofc) instead of coffee. thinking of this on the warm fall day in nyc! 🍁
Brunch DJs? A rainbow fun mimosa flight? A board with as many miscellaneous noshes as you can imagine? @wtf_sushi_nyc has it all. Check it out for so much fun! 🎉🥂
going to @deldottowine is like going to Disneyland for me. I literally love it so much, their wines are spectacular, and I can’t recommend the experience enough🍷

📍Maple & Ash, Scottsdale
⭐️9.9/10 
I loved @mapleandash when I went in Chicago, so on my recent trip to Scottsdale, I knew I had to try, and this location is just as good as the other. The agnolotti was shockingly SPECTACULAR, the caviar French onion dip was delicious, and the prickly pear martini welcome cocktail was perfection 💓the meatballs were also tender and flavorful, and the steak was great as always. we split the cowboy ribeye.
highly recommend @_prive_nyc ! affordable coffee and really cool experiences, and amazing staff! 🤍🥂

Had the BEST time checking out @thewoowoonyc 🥂 This midtown speakeasy was so fun, and not one to miss. We loved our drinks, the staff was so nice, and it was such a cool experience. Highly recommend, thanks for having me! 🪩

📍Bonnie’s, Williamsburg 
⭐️9.0/10
I’m a big fan of @bonniesbrooklyn ! On my second trip back multiple things wowed me that I didn’t try the first time- including the amazing shrimp, espresso martini, and sundaes. The more I try the better it gets. Such a great spot, highly recommend 🍨🍤
Had a blast checking out @themeanfiddler , especially trying all the fun new Christmas drinks 🎄🤶 the staff is so nice, it’s packed (even on a Wednesday), and so decorated. Thank you for having me!

📍Jacks Wife Freda, Soho
⭐️8.8/10
Really enjoyed the famous @jackswifefreda brunch in soho! While the rosewater waffle lacked, the rest hit the spot. Delicious and flavorful, and a great atmosphere. If you can get in, worth the go!
Had such a great time at @thedickensnyc 🥳 highly recommend taking part of this insane bottomless dinner, deal, who doesn’t wanna get drunk on a weekday for $25?! 🤑🍹

finally made it to @cucinaalba ! 🍸 the space in the lantern building is so nice, the pastas were delicious (have to have the agnolotti), and it’s totally worth the visit. reservations aren’t impossible finally, and the staff is kind. have you been⁉️ #cucinaalba

I could eat the @thenookeastvillage beef tartare every day. it is excellent. they also have my favorite cocktail in nyc, the boom cocktail! it’s chamomile infused gin, st.germain, green grape, and yuzu cocktail🍹 thinking about that app today… 💭

Famous off menu shawarma from @auzaatar ! They may say it’s for 2-3 but it would be WAY too much for 2, we did it with 4. Fries have good spice, meat is yummy, but your table gets HOT with the heat from the shawarma but it’s def worth the try. Also, please don’t blow up this spot, because it’s one of the best last minute reservation restaurants I’ve found in nyc! 💛

📍Golden Diner
⭐️9.7/10
Holy sh*t! You all know there’s rarely a place I think is worth the hype but golden diner is worth it all and more. These pancakes (berry compote a must) are out of this world, and the chicken katsu hit the spot. There’s so much more I want to try and will be running back.
I realized I hadn’t had a good cheeseburger in SO long so was so happy to finally try @fairfaxnyc ! delicious, well priced, and you can ACTUALLY get in… 🍔 👀 run don’t walk to Fairfax 💕

📍Semma, West village 
⭐️6.9/10
🚨HOT TAKE ALERT🚨 @semmanyc had an amazing dosa, and delicious cocktail, but the rest of our dishes didn’t stand out to me. part of it I think it was too spicy for me, so I wasn’t the right demographic! if you wanna go, they reserve their bar seats for walk-ins! so just go out your name down super early and you can get in 🫶🏼

thank you for having me @barriotaqueria !🌮 everyone truly was so happy, and that really stood out to me (maybe the fun drinks in crazy cups help😂🍹) do NOT skip out on the churros at the end of the meal, def my fav item🔥

had to follow up my trip to @barriotaqueria with a trip to the @reddistrictny !❤️ let me tell you… these fun glasses and cocktails🍹 have GENEROUS pours- red district gets you drunk so it’s a good value spot too ✅

📍Laser Wolf, Brooklyn
⭐️8.8/10
Finally went back to @laserwolf_bk and I’m glad I did! I liked my experience, and it’s a super solid restaurant. Enjoyed my salmon way more over the meat I had last time, and felt it was a more generous portion. Going in the winter is a bit more of a bummer because it’s covered with a clear slip so you can’t see the amazing view, but it’s still cool. + the included post dinner ice cream is amazing. If you can get in, go!

📍Sandwell, UWS
Loved checking out @getsandwell in the UWS! The healthyISH sandwich shop was so good- my favorite was the meatball sub, made with turkey meatball.🥪 The spot is also super affordable as the subs were all $11-$13… which is AMAZING! Don’t know the last time I saw sandwiches this big for that price 🤤 #sandwell
finally got to try @the_happytuna that everyone’s been talking about! highly, highly, HIGHLY recommend their nigiri box🍣🍱

📍Parm, UWS
⭐️7.8/10
Carbones cheaper sidekick is another @majorfoodgroup hit. The spicy rig is delicious, and while not the same caliber as carbons, hits the spot while needed. It’s unpretentious and delicious.
@tooomuchfoood knows all the best spots so of course @thepnewyork lived up to all her hype! absolutely loved the vibe and my food (especiallyyyyyy the pad see ew). great gem in the UES! 💎

📍Funke, Beverly Hills
⭐️9.9/10
Ended 2023 with one of the best meals I had all year, @funke_la ! Funke was exceptional, and @evanfunke was there himself making the agnolotti 🧑‍🍳 the focaccia was like eating a cloud ☁️, the pasta was flavorful, fabulous, and melt in your mouth, and the prawns with garlic were out of this world (pro tip dip the focaccia in the prawns sauce 🤫 )  highly, highly, highly recommend!🔥

location.city_name: The Polo Bar - A Ralph Lauren Restaurant

social_posts.post_text: @laruanapaisanyc in queens was such a nice time!🫶🏼 the drinks were so yummy, and strong, especially the frozen light up pina colada x sangria (yeah you read that right).🍹 the staff is super nice, they have a HUGE menu with all your Colombian favorites, and I felt like I was back in Miami.🥹 Had to add La Bicicleta by Carlos Vives & Shakira over this post bc I have had it on REPEAT since our lunch.🚲 Their playlist was amazing, and they steamed all the music videos too which I love. Such an awesome spot😇

📍4 Charles, West Village
⭐️9.9/10
I felt so cool FINALLY getting to visit @nycprimerib , and let me say, it lives up to ALL the hype.🔥 We had the king cut prime rib and it was flavorful and generous, the burger was tender and juicy and delicious (didn’t get any add ons), we had fried with the BEST garlic aioli ever, elote which was a little spicier than I would’ve liked, the prime dip, and the thick cut bacon.🫶🏼 Then for dessert (which was AMAZING) we had the lemon meringue pie, their iconic sundae that just HIT the spot, and the best chocolate pie I’ve ever had.🍰 P.S. we also had a chocolate martini with dessert, and there’s no better way to describe it than it SLAPPED.🍫 Highly recommend. Sleeper menu item.👀 then of course also had to have a martini 🍸

Had never had fajitas before @lamorranyc and now I have been craving them for a week they were so yummy and flavorful.😍 The space was super cute, staff was nice and efficient, and drinks were yummy! 🍹you’ve gotta go to La Morra, and when you do, don’t skip the fajitas or the super strong cocktails...👀

📍Best Pizza, Williamsburg
⭐️9.2/10
When you go to best pizza you feel like you’re transported to old school New York. With classic signs and decor, this spot hits. Whole place smells amazing like their pizzas, and the grandma slice was heavily. Crunchy crust, perfect balance of flavor, and I highly recommend 🍕
